This paper deals with the problem of biological image analysis, specifically lineage tracing. The proposed solution involves an integer linear program (ILP) with path-cut inequalities to enforce the morality of lineages. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image analysis. Additionally, the use of an ILP suggests that the paper may also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The paper also proposes efficient separation procedures and a branch-and-cut algorithm, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of real microscopy data suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
